The following procedures are done upon receipt of PPE, viz:

At the time an item of non-expendable personal property is received by the Municipality, the item shall be assigned a PIN and a tag containing this number shall be permanently affixed to the item, in a conspicuous place;
2.  Upon conduct of actual count of PPE, the inventory committee shall physically identify the property item by identification number, description, and serial number. The location and responsible department shall be noted on the inventory sheet. The physical condition of the item shall also be noted; 
3.  If any property items are located, which are not tagged, these items shall be tagged immediately;
4.  In case of transfer of accountability of PPE from one AO to another, the transfer must be effected through Invoice Receipt for Property;
5.   Record only PPE items to which the Municipality has legal right over them;
6.  ARE form must contain information on acquisition date and cost/value of the PPE; and
7.  The GSO must reconcile its recorded PPE with the Accounting Department at least quarterly.

1.The Municipal Accountant and Treasurer shall coordinate to regularly reconcile the Cash book and General/Subsidiary ledger balances to immediately record/correct entries made;

2.The Municipal Accountant shall prepare and record the adjusting journal entries in the appropriate books of the concerned fund to revert back the amount of the issued check which has become stale to the cash in bank account and establish the liability of the municipality; and

3.The Municipal Treasurer shall record all transactions for the day immediately and at the end of each day the debit and credit shall be closed and ruled and the balances carried forward as opening balances of the Cash Book for the next day.

